                <article class="blog-post" onclick="togglePost(this)">
                    <h3>Getting Started with GRC: A Beginner's Journey</h3>
                    <div class="meta">Posted on December 1, 2024 | Governance, Risk & Compliance</div>
                    <p class="excerpt">Understanding the fundamentals of Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) is essential for any cybersecurity professional...</p>
                    <div class="full-content">
                        <p>Understanding the fundamentals of Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) is essential for any cybersecurity professional. GRC provides the framework that helps organizations manage security risks, meet regulatory requirements, and maintain effective governance structures.</p>
                        <p>In this post, I'll share my learning path, including key frameworks like NIST, ISO 27001, and why GRC matters in today's threat landscape. Whether you're new to cybersecurity or looking to specialize in GRC, understanding these fundamentals will set you up for success.</p>
                        <p>Key takeaways: Start with understanding your organization's risk appetite, learn the major compliance frameworks relevant to your industry, and always document your processes.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="read-more">Read more →</span>
                </article>

                <article class="blog-post" onclick="togglePost(this)">
                    <h3>Top 5 Free Resources for Cybersecurity Learners</h3>
                    <div class="meta">Posted on November 28, 2024 | Learning Resources</div>
                    <p class="excerpt">Finding quality, free resources to learn cybersecurity can be challenging. Here are my top picks that have helped me on my journey...</p>
                    <div class="full-content">
                        <p>Finding quality, free resources to learn cybersecurity can be challenging. Here are my top picks that have helped me on my journey:</p>
                        <p>1. TryHackMe - Interactive labs for hands-on practice<br>
                        2. OWASP - Essential web application security knowledge<br>
                        3. NIST Cybersecurity Framework - Industry-standard documentation<br>
                        4. Cybersecurity & Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) - Government resources and training<br>
                        5. YouTube channels like NetworkChuck and John Hammond</p>
                        <p>These resources cover everything from technical skills to compliance and policy understanding. The best part? They're all completely free and regularly updated.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="read-more">Read more →</span>
                </article>

                <article class="blog-post" onclick="togglePost(this)">
                    <h3>Understanding Risk Assessments in Cybersecurity</h3>
                    <div class="meta">Posted on November 25, 2024 | Risk Management</div>
                    <p class="excerpt">Risk assessments are a cornerstone of effective cybersecurity programs. Let's break down the process and why it matters...</p>
                    <div class="full-content">
                        <p>Risk assessments are a cornerstone of effective cybersecurity programs. Let's break down the process and why it matters.</p>
                        <p>A proper risk assessment involves identifying assets, determining threats and vulnerabilities, analyzing the potential impact, and prioritizing remediation efforts. It's not just about finding problems—it's about understanding which problems matter most to your organization.</p>
                        <p>The key is to be systematic: document everything, use a consistent methodology (like NIST SP 800-30), and remember that risk assessment is an ongoing process, not a one-time project. Regular reassessments ensure your security posture keeps pace with evolving threats.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="read-more">Read more →</span>
                </article>
